    <text>
        <body>
            <div type="edition">
                <div type="textpart">
                    <ab>Ego <persName key="#Witness #Princeps" ref="#people/3010">secundus
                            Riccardus</persName>, gratia Dei Capuanorum <rs key="#Princeps"
                            >princeps</rs>, haec <rs key="#Cartula">cartula</rs> recordationis
                        describere praecepi de intentione, quae, cum pluribus vicibus, fuerat inter
                        dominum <persName key="#Bishops" ref="#people/3056">Ioannem</persName>,
                            <placeName key="#Cities" ref="#places/4000">Aversanum</placeName>
                        <rs key="#Bishops">episcopum</rs>, et dominum <persName key="#Abbots"
                            ref="#people/3016">Guarinum</persName>, <rs key="#Abbots">abbatem</rs>
                        <rs key="#Monasteries">monasterii</rs>
                        <orgName key="#Monasteries" ref="#juridical_persons/3000">Sancti
                            Laurentii</orgName>, de <placeName ref="#places/701"
                            key="#Lakes #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Mention #Ports #Fluvial_transport #Public_exactions #Rights_of_use_on_woods/pastures/waters #Privileges"
                            >Patria</placeName>, quomodo, in mense aprilis, videlicet die dominico,
                        quarto die intrantis, in octava pascae, in meo palatio, <persName
                            ref="#people/2498" key="#Marquis/duke">Rogerius</persName>
                        <rs key="#Marquis/duke">dux</rs> finivit et stabilivit inter eos: sit ut ego
                        et barones meos, et episcopum, et abbatem predictum, et <persName
                            key="#Witness" ref="#people/3078">Stantio</persName>, vice mea, eamus ad
                        Patriam, et coniurarem ego eodem Stantio, sub nomine fidis et sacramenti,
                        mihi ab eo facto, ut quae in Patria <rs key="#parentOf">pater</rs> meus
                        habebat tunc temporis quando donum fecerat Sancto Laurentio diceret, et ita
                        permaneret, ut intentione ipsa in aeternum decisa fuisset, quod utrique
                        parti fieri complacuit, et ego cum eis constitui. Quadam vero die veneris,
                        octavo die stantis mense aprilis, ad Patriam profecti sumus, coniurato
                        itaque a me Stantione, uti dux praeceperat, testificatus est ut quam pater
                        meus in Patriam habebat quando donum fecerat <rs key="#Natural_landscape"
                            >cripta</rs>
                        <placeName
                            key="#Natural_landscape #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Function #Redistributive #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Public_exactions"
                            ref="#places/4084">Camilca</placeName>, cum pertinentia sua, idest cum
                            <rs
                            key="#Natural_landscape #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Function #Redistributive #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure"
                            >criptis</rs>, quae circa ea sunt, et <rs
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Function #Redistributive #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Ports"
                            >portum</rs>
                        <placeName key="#Ports #Public_exactions" ref="#places/4085"
                            >Moritani</placeName>, et <rs
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Function #Redistributive #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Ports"
                            >portum</rs> de <placeName ref="#places/2805"
                            key="#Ports #Public_exactions">Cre</placeName>, et <rs
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Function #Redistributive #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Ports"
                            >portum</rs>
                        <placeName key="#Ports #Public_exactions" ref="#places/4086"
                            >Porani</placeName> et <rs
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Function #Redistributive #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Ports"
                            >portum</rs>
                        <placeName key="#Ports #Public_exactions" ref="#places/4087">Cupulisi de
                            Abitici</placeName>, et <rs
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Function #Redistributive #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Ports"
                            >portum</rs> de <placeName
                            key="#Ports #Public_exactions #Rights_of_use_on_woods/pastures/waters"
                            ref="#places/4088">Avena</placeName>, et <rs
                            key="#Rights_of_use_on_woods/pastures/waters">partem suam aquae</rs>,
                        usque ad <placeName key="#Ports #Public_exactions" ref="#places/4089"
                            >Altezze</placeName>, et <rs
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Function #Redistributive #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Ports"
                            >portum</rs> ipsum quietum, et <placeName
                            key="#Villages/settlements #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Function #Redistributive #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Public_exactions"
                            ref="#places/5152">lagnulum</placeName>, et <placeName
                            key="#Villages/settlements #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Function #Redistributive #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Public_exactions"
                            ref="#places/5153">calvarolam</placeName>, et <placeName
                            ref="#places/4090"
                            key="#Villages/settlements #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Function #Redistributive #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Public_exactions"
                            >Lartiati</placeName>, et <rs
                            key="#Rights_of_use_on_woods/pastures/waters #Privileges">Patriam
                            quietam habebat die mercurii, et die veneris, quod nemo audebat piscari
                            in ea nisi pro principe, sine piscatoribus fucis, et in caeteris aliis
                            diebus epdomadae, per unumquodque diem, piscatores ad castaldeum
                            principis dabant, causa honoris, <rs key="#Fish">de magnis piscibus
                                unum</rs>, et pro se similiter unum, et si non habebant magnos
                            pisces aut forsitan celabant ei illos, ipse principis <rs
                                key="#Gastaldus/vicegastaldus">castaldeus</rs> capiebat de magnis
                            piscibus unum, valens duobus maioribus, et de <rs key="#Fish"
                                >anecosa</rs> duodecim suscipiebat, et <rs key="#Fish"
                                >anguillas</rs>, et de unoquoque <rs key="#Fluvial_transport"
                                >lintre</rs> de <rs key="#Fish">spedone pisces</rs> duodecim</rs>.
                        Et <rs key="#Fisheries #Fish">tres paraturas </rs>de <placeName
                            ref="#places/4078" key="#Villages/settlements #Fisheries #Fish"
                            >Casale</placeName> erant quietas principis, et homines monachorum
                        similiter; et de <rs key="#Ports">portu</rs>
                        <rs key="#Natural_landscape">fucis</rs>, et de cripta Camilca, et portu
                        Moretani, et Cre, et Porani, et de portu Cupulisi de Abitici, et de Avena,
                        et Altezze, cum pertinentia sua, usque ad Patriam habebat princeps, per
                        unumquodque annum, <rs key="#Value #Public_exactions">tarenos
                            octingentos</rs>; et in istis portibus non audebat aliquis homo pisces
                        emere vel venundare usque ad mare, nisi ipsi qui octingentos tarenos
                        principi dabant. Hoc testimonium reddidit Stantio, vice mea, in praedicto
                        die veneris, ante me <persName key="#Witness #Princeps" ref="#people/3010"
                            >Richardum</persName> principem,<persName key="#Witness #siblingOf"
                            ref="#people/3022"> Ioffridum Iordani</persName>
                        <rs key="#siblingOf">fratrem</rs> meum, <persName key="#Witness"
                            ref="#people/5046">Ioffridum de Ponte Indulfi</persName>, <persName
                            key="#Witness" ref="#people/5016">Thomam de Venabili</persName>,
                            <persName key="#Witness" ref="#people/5017">Rainaldus de
                            Magdaloni</persName>, <persName key="#Witness" ref="#people/5030">Yon de
                            Doeli</persName>, <persName key="#Witness"><name
                                ref="Ivanus f. Cansolini">Iuanum filium Gonsolini</name></persName>,
                            <persName key="#Witness"><name ref="Guarinus f. Guascolini">Guarinum
                                filium Guascolimi</name></persName>, <persName key="#Witness #Judge"
                            ref="#people/3012">Quiriacum</persName>
                        <rs key="#Judge">iudicem</rs>, <persName key="#Witness"><name ref="Pando"
                                >Pandonem</name></persName>, <persName key="#Witness"><name
                                ref="Wilielmus Brunus">Guillielmum Brunum</name></persName>,
                            <persName key="#Witness"><name ref="Petrus de Aversa">Petrum de
                                Aversa</name></persName>, <persName key="#Witness"><name
                                ref="Gotefredus f. Ermenloth">Ioffridum filium
                            Hermenioth</name></persName>, <persName key="#Witness"><name
                                ref="Ernulfus de Principato">Ernolfum de
                            Principato</name></persName>, <rs key="#Witness #Abbots">abbatem</rs>
                        <orgName ref="#juridical_persons/3052">Sancti Salvatoris Telensis</orgName>,
                            <persName key="#Witness #Priests"><name ref="Maurus"
                            >Maurum</name></persName>
                        <rs key="#Priests">presbiterum</rs>, <persName key="#Witness"><name
                                ref="Iohannes Lidulfi">Ioannem Lidulfi</name></persName>, <persName
                            key="#Witness #Other_clerics"><name ref="Wilielmus">Guillielmum
                            </name></persName><rs key="#Other_clerics">clericum</rs>, <rs
                            key="#Deacons">Iaconum</rs>
                        <persName key="#Witness #Deacons"><name ref="Iohannes"
                            >Ioannem</name></persName>. In anno Domincae incarnationis .MCI., et
                        vicesimo primo anno principatus, per indictionem nonam.</ab>
                </div>
            </div>
